Marine National Park

The Twelve Apostles Marine National park

The Twelve Apostles Marine National Park protects a diverse range of species that can be found in the shallow and intertidal reefs and which have been found to have the Victoria’s greatest diversity of invertebrates on limestone reefs.


Weedy Sea Dragon which are native to the Australian coastal waters and are very bony fish. They are most commonly found in a thin strip of shallow water along the coastline.

Little penguins' arrival time to go hunting can vary with the seasons, but the find it’s best to arrive in time for sunset, the penguins typically begin to emerge from the sea 10 to 15 minutes after sunset, with the majority arriving about 20 to 25 minutes later as twilight transitions to darkness. As they return, you’ll notice their lively interactions, including the odd territorial dispute.

Seals that live around the Twelve Apostles inhabit the rocky reefs and coastlines often spot seals, along with other wildlife like birds, penguins and other marine life in the area.
